          <title>NFL projects salary cap between $277.5M and $281.5M in 2025, rising by as much as $26M</title>
          <description><![CDATA[NEW YORK (AP) — The NFL salary cap will be between $277.5 million and $281.5 million for the 2025 season, rising as much as $26 million from last year. The bump is great news for Cincinnati, which is hoping to sign receiver Tee Higgins to a long-term contract.]]></description>
